(7, 'calculators', 'calculators', '', '', '', '', 0, 0),
(8, 'advice', 'advice', '', '', '', '', 0, 0),
(9, 'resales homes', 'resales-homes', '', '<div class="resale_homes_box_one">\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-12">\r\n<p>According to homula there are three types of real estate transactions. The words short sales and foreclosures have become synonymous with great deals. However, there are fundamental differences between them and it&rsquo;s important that you understand the differences before investing. Remember that cheap does not always mean that it is a deal; it could be cheap for another reason. In addition, always have an exit strategy in mind when you are buying. MLS listing also indicates that there are three kinds of real estate transactions:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="traditional_sale"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="http://realestate.homula.com/wp-content/themes/realsite/images/resale-homes-icon-1.png" /><span>1. Traditional sale</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="short_sale"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="http://realestate.homula.com/wp-content/themes/realsite/images/resale-homes-icon-2.png" /><span>2. Short sale</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="foceclosure_or_bank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="http://realestate.homula.com/wp-content/themes/realsite/images/resale-homes-icon-3.png" /><span>3. Foreclosure or bank-owned property</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="resale_homes_box_two">\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="resale_homes_img_left"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="http://realestate.homula.com/wp-content/themes/realsite/images/resale-homes-images-1.png" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="resale_homes_content">\r\n<h3 class="resale_homes_h3_left">Traditional sale</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The traditional sale is the type of sale that you are used to if you have ever purchased a property. It involves two parties, the buyers and sellers. The sellers may or may not have a mortgage on their property but the important thing to understand is that the amount of the note or mortgage does not exceed the sale price of the property. In this case the sellers at their sole discretion can sell the property at a price that is convenient for them and do not need third-party or lender approval to do so, because the proceeds from the sale more than cover all expenses including the repayment of the note.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="resale_homes_box_three">\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="resale_homes_img_right"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="http://realestate.homula.com/wp-content/themes/realsite/images/resale-homes-images-2.png" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="resale_homes_content">\r\n<h3 class="resale_homes_h3_right">Short Sale</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Adjustable Rate Mortgage (ARM), where after five years the rate adjusted to prime plus 5 percent. Fast forward five years, Mr. Smith loses his job, and to make matters worse his mortgage payments tripled overnight because of the adjustment in rate. Now the family definitely can&rsquo;t afford the new mortgage payments and are forced to sell their home. Unfortunately, because of market conditions and declining property values, it would be impossible for them to sell their house for the amount of the mortgage. Therefore, they are selling the property for a shortfall which constitutes a short sale. Very simplistically, a short sale means when there is a sale and the person owes more on the property than the property is worth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="resale_homes_box_four">\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="resale_homes_img_left"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="http://realestate.homula.com/wp-content/themes/realsite/images/resale-homes-images-3.png" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="resale_homes_content">\r\n<h3 class="resale_homes_h3_left">Foreclosure or bank-owned property</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Toronto real estate brokers a foreclosure is a property where the note bearer has forcefully evicted the inhabitants for nonpayment of their mortgages. Basically if we take the previous example with the smith family and assume they stopped paying their mortgage, eventually they would be driven out of their home and bank would take over the property. Since lenders are not in the business of owing property, they proceed to sell the property in as is condition on the open market. Bank properties are often the fastest deals to close, but have their own challenges because they are often properties that have not been lived in for a while. These properties need attention to bring them up to the living standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Homula has helped many people across Canada to achieve their goals in the real estate market. We would like to stress the importance of working with reputable real estate professionals. The professionals that you surround yourself with in making this important choice can make a world of difference.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our philosophy is that decisions are always better made when you are well informed of the process; it never hurts to be too well informed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Purchasing a brand new, newly constructed home is an appealing prospect for some, but if you&rsquo;re not dead-set on a fresh home, resale homes are a great choice that can still offer you the opportunity to live in your dream home. However, should know exactly what you&rsquo;re getting yourself into when purchasing one, and our Toronto real estate experts are here to educate you on everything you need to know about them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Replacement Costs:</strong> While in newly constructed homes everything is new, resale homes have been in use for a while, meaning components such as the furnace, water heater and air conditioning unit could be past their prime. Always do you research on these components and get a feel for when each unit is going to need replacing and how much it will cost. This will save you the hassle of purchasing a home that you love, only to realize that you need to invest thousands of dollars into replacement costs. Typical improvements include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Heating and air conditioning<br />\r\n&bull; Flooring and carpeting<br />\r\n&bull; Exterior and interior painting<br />\r\n&bull; Remodeling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Energy Consumption: One of the biggest appeals of newly constructed homes is their energy efficiency. Many of them come with energy certifications that cover walls, roofs windows, doors and appliance packages and have to meet tougher energy efficiency standards than older homes. If you value the importance of investing in something &ldquo;green,&rdquo; resale homes might not be the best option for you as many of them were built years ago when energy standards were much lower.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Resale Value: Are you planning on selling your home in the future? Newly constructed homes are typically more desirable and thus have a higher resale value than older homes, making them a better choice for those that plan to sell their home at some point. However, this is not always the case &ndash; with some hard work and the proper renovations, you can significantly bolster your homes resale value.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Negotiation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the big advantages of purchasing a resale home is the flexibility that you will have during the negotiation process. Everything from closing dates to prices can be negotiated and with the help of an experienced realtor, you can really knock down the price of your investment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Deposit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrary to new construction homes, the deposits for resale homes are much more affordable at the time of agreement. Although these deposits vary depending on the price of the home in question, they typically range from $1,000 to $10,000, compared to $5,000 to $40,000 for new construction homes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Extra Features</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although we touched on the nature of replacement costs above, a great deal of resale homes have been renovated with extra features, meaning if you find the right one you can benefit from newly installed air conditioning or a finished basement. When purchasing a newly constructed home, tacking on additional renovations comes out of your own pocket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So you&rsquo;ve decided that you want a resale home?</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', 1, 0),
(10, 'exclusive homes', 'exclusive-homes', '', '<div class="container">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-12">\r\n<form action="http://homula.idxbroker.com/idx/search/basic" class="exclusive_homes_form" method="post">\r\n<div class="input-group">\r\n<p>At Homula, our <strong>Toronto real estate </strong>agents are dedicated to connecting you with luxurious and exclusive homes. There is no specific size, design or style that defines what a luxury home is. A luxury home could be a 30,000 square foot mansion, or a 2,500 square foot home that features intricate crown moulding throughout the interior. Searching for a luxury <strong>MLS listing</strong> is not an easy task for the average person.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In most cases, only a <a href="http://realestate.homula.com/agents/"><strong>qualified real estate agent</strong></a>&nbsp;has access to an exclusive listing. Many sellers avoid putting pictures and information about their properties on the internet in order to protect their privacy. If the listing does happen to appear on MLS, the word &ldquo;exclusive&rdquo; will appear instead of the cost of the house. In this case, your real estate agent will have to contact the listing agent in order to inquire about the price of the home and work out a deal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you decide to purchase a luxury home, you should take heed to the following tips:</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="row exclusive_homes_wr">\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>Due Diligence</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Given the fact that all real estate investments could either make or break your pocket, it is imperative for you to hire an expert <strong><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/home-inspector/">home inspector</a></strong>&nbsp;prior to purchase. Luxury home are often large, and will require the eyes and knowledge of an expert. Apart from the items and features included in many homes, an expert may also need to inspect:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lawn irrigation systems</li>\r\n	<li>Indoor movie theatre</li>\r\n	<li>Landscape lighting</li>\r\n	<li>Spas and Pools</li>\r\n	<li>Exterior fireplaces</li>\r\n	<li>Heated driveways/floors</li>\r\n	<li>Surveillance and security systems</li>\r\n	<li>Awning systems</li>\r\n	<li>Automatic screens</li>\r\n	<li>Central vacuum systems</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>Photos Aren&rsquo;t Everything</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Many large homes aren&rsquo;t as photogenic as you might think, so don&rsquo;t dismiss them purely based on their front elevation photos. Once you narrow down the choices that are most appealing to you, take a trip to see them in person &ndash; sometimes you really have the get up close and personal to really appreciate what they have to offer.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>Evaluation</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you manage to get a close look at some luxury homes, evaluate your options closely. Take note of everything from construction methods and architectural highlights to security systems. Evaluating a luxury home is a much more detailed process than a standard home, so be prepared to get highly involved if you want to uncover every little detail of the potential properties and make the right purchasing decision.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>Financing</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Compared to smaller mortgages, the loan process for buying a luxury home takes quite a while. Even if you have stellar credit and a very high income, it could take up to 60 days to secure a loan. To speed up the process, it is recommended that you contact a reputable <strong><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/mortgage-broker/">mortgage broker</a></strong>&nbsp;so that they can get you pre-approved earlier on in the process.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>Title Insurance</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Always invest in title insurance to ensure your protection against any problems that are forgotten. In addition, make sure to take a look at the exceptions page of the title insurance process prior to closing and run it buy your agent to make sure that everything covered in it is crystal clear.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>Contact an Expert Real Estate Agent</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The importance of contacting an expert real estate agent cannot be stressed enough. They know exactly how to find you all of the information you need. In addition to this, and as mentioned before, they have access to information that is not posted on the internet. Real estate agents are timely, professional and extremely knowledgeable.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>TIP: Use a Local Agent!</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to luxury homes, using a local real estate agent is very beneficial. These agents will be very familiar with the area that you want to buy in and since there&rsquo;s a higher degree of control over access to high-end properties, you&rsquo;re going to want one who can easily connect you with the open houses and appointments needed to see them in person.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>The Search Process</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the main reasons that an agent is so essential for luxury homes lies in the fact that many of them are unlisted in order to protect the seller&rsquo;s privacy. Many of these exclusive properties can only be found through the personal networks of realtors, making MLS of no help to you. Using the connections of an experienced agent can greatly benefit you during the search process and expand your options beyond what is on standard search engines and listings.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>Patience Is a Virtue</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>At the end of the day, patience is one of the most beneficial traits to have during the process of purchasing a luxury home. These homes are a big financial obligation and you don&rsquo;t want to make a hasty decision that you&rsquo;ll later regret. Take your time when considering your options and gather as much information as you can about each potential home. Consult with your agent regularly and don&rsquo;t be afraid of passing up good homes, because chances are you&rsquo;re going to need to give up on a few &ndash; it&rsquo;s all part of the process.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<div class="exclusive_homes_box">\r\n<h4>Luxury</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The Luxury real estate market has experienced a record amount of growth over the last few years and continuously grows on a daily basis. With international buyers seeking to take advantage of ideal exchange rates, you can expect this growth to continue well into the future. Don&rsquo;t miss out on the opportunity to invest in a luxury home just because you don&rsquo;t know how to approach the process or have the help that you need. Contact an expert agent today in order to find the home of your dreams!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</form>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', 1, 0),
(11, 'open house', 'open-house', '', '<div class="stbg_1">\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<div class="shadow_bottom">\r\n<div class="header_form">\r\n<form action="http://homula.idxbroker.com/idx/search/basic" method="post">\r\n<div class="input-group"><span class="input-group-btn"><button class="btn btn-simple only-icon" type="submit"><i class="fa fa-search"></i>Open House Search</button></span></div>\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n<p>Our Toronto real estate agents are experts at organizing open houses! We have connections with interior designers, furniture rental companies and other industry experts.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="stbg_2">\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<h3><span class="tittle_style">How to organize an open house?</span></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul class="nav nav-tabs">\r\n	<li class="active"><a data-toggle="tab" href="#advertising">Advertising</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#organization">Organization</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#clean_up">Clean Up</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#last_minute_fixes">Last Minute Fixes</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-content">\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade in active" id="advertising"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Every single avenue of marketing should be considered for an open house. This includes:</span>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class="list_icon"><i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Flyers</li>\r\n	<li class="list_icon"><i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Ads in the local newspaper</li>\r\n	<li class="list_icon"><i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>All forms of social media</li>\r\n	<li class="list_icon"><i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Postings online</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">When you host an open house, inform your neighbours. Invite them and ask them to bring anyone they know who is looking to purchase a home. This allows prospective buyers to have a chat with the locals in person when they are viewing the home. They will get a clear idea of the type of locality and community the home has to offer. The surrounding neighbourhood is a big factor buyers consider before they make a purchase.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="organization">\r\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">The marketing campaign for an open house should always start a week in advance. This gives potential buyers time to reshuffle their schedule, in order to make the event. The scheduled date of the open house should never conflict with major sporting or local civic events. This increases the chances of having more attendees. When you host the event, ask a friend or family member to help. Always have someone at the front door to greet new arrivals. This generates a friendly, casual atmosphere while leaving you and your agent free to show the house to the visitors who are already present. Hand out flyers to everyone who visits, the fliers should have clear pictures and contact information for yourself and your agent. If possible, have a professional photographers take the pictures of the house.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="clean_up">\r\n<p style="font-weight: 400;">Make sure that the house is not just neat and tidy but absolutely spotless, especially the kitchen and bathrooms because these are the rooms that could potentially make or break a sale. For the viewings, try to use as much natural light as possible, open the drapes in every single room. If you have pets, leave them with a friend at least a few days in advance. Remove any litter boxes and vacuum up any loose strands of fur that may be lying around. Another important thing to remember is to always put away items of value. If you have valuable decorations, do not leave them in plain view. <b><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/about-us/">Our professionals</a> </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;agree that theft is a surprisingly common occurrence at an open house. The last thing to remember is to refrain from giving out personal information to prospective buyers. Try not to let details about why you are selling the home slip out during casual conversation. Little tit bits of information can be used as a bargaining chip during final negotiations. </span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="last_minute_fixes">\r\n<p>When it&rsquo;s getting down to the wire, make sure that everything is set to really &ldquo;wow&rdquo; your prospective buyers. Pick up after any pets that you have, open up your curtains to let some light in and keep some windows open to freshen up the environment. In addition, make sure that all of your driveways and walk areas are clear and safe for all of your visitors.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="stbg_1">\r\n<div class="container">&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span class="tittle_style">Why organize an open house?</span></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>It might seem like a lot of unnecessary work, but organizing an open house offers numerous benefits that can draw in buyers and help you find the right one for your home. Some of these benefits include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="nav nav-tabs">\r\n	<li class="active"><a data-toggle="tab" href="#more_buyers">More Buyers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#setting_scene">Setting the Scene</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#interested_buyer">Interested Buyers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#comparison">Comparison</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-content">\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade in active" id="more_buyers">\r\n<p>Open houses are a great way to draw in potential buyers that would otherwise have been too unmotivated to book a showing. In addition, they draw in visitors in a more diverse amount of ways than a standard listing. Ask your family and friends to spread the word to people they think would be interested in purchasing your home and make sure to invest in some advertising and <strong><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/sign-suppliers/">signage</a></strong> to rope in as many potential buyers as possible, both casual and serious.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="setting_scene">\r\n<p>Traditional showings can be stressful and require lots of upkeep when it comes to keeping your home clean and ready for any potential showings. Open houses give you plenty of time to prepare your home and make it &ldquo;show ready&rdquo; in advance as you&rsquo;ll know exactly when your prospective buyers are going to be in your home. They&rsquo;re a great way to minimize the amount of cleaning you need to do while at the same time maximizing the amount of prospective buyers that get to see your home.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="interested_buyer">\r\n<p>For buyers who are already interested in your home, open houses are a better way for them to come and get a look at it in a less formal manner when compared to private showings. It&rsquo;s a great way for them to look around without feeling rushed and even bring some friends and family along to get a second opinion. With a bit of luck, you could lock in a potential buyer that otherwise might have not asked for another showing.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="comparison">\r\n<p>Certain locations will have no shortage of open houses on weekends, making them a great way for you to show off your home and really set it apart from the competition. Many buyers will likely be stopping by more than one open house and comparing the benefits of each, so focus on making your home stand out and highlight the ways that it&rsquo;s different from the competition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most people just turn to the internet when they are looking to buy or sell something. Although the open house has become the tradition of a bygone era, if it is marketed correctly and professionally advertised, it can be a very effective marketing tool. A good open house can draw in prospective buyers that you otherwise would have missed out on and give you the opportunity to set yourself apart from the local competition.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', 1, 0),
