(14, 'list my house', 'list-my-house', '', '<div class="container">\n    <div class="row">\n        <div class="col-sm-12">\n            <div role="form" class="wpcf7" id="wpcf7-f1844-p545-o1" lang="en-US" dir="ltr">\n                <div class="screen-reader-response"></div>\n                <form action="/list-my-house/#wpcf7-f1844-p545-o1" method="post" class="wpcf7-form ng-pristine ng-valid">\n                    <div style="display: none;">\n                        <input type="hidden" name="_wpcf7" value="1844">\n                        <input type="hidden" name="_wpcf7_version" value="4.5.1">\n                        <input type="hidden" name="_wpcf7_locale" value="en_US">\n                        <input type="hidden" name="_wpcf7_unit_tag" value="wpcf7-f1844-p545-o1">\n                        <input type="hidden" name="_wpnonce" value="e4c301bf96">\n                    </div>\n                    <div class="col-sm-8">\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>Your Name (required)</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap your-name"><input type="text" name="your-name" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>Address (required)</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap address"><input type="text" name="address" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>City (required)</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap city"><input type="text" name="city" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>Postal Code (required)</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap postal-code"><input type="text" name="postal-code" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>Phone Number (required)</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap phone-number"><input type="text" name="phone-number" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>Square Footage (required)</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap square-footage"><input type="text" name="square-footage" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>House Type (required)</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap house-type"><input type="text" name="house-type" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>Price (required)</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap price"><input type="number" name="price" value="" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-number wpcf7-validates-as-required wpcf7-validates-as-number" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>Your Email (required)</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap your-email"><input type="email" name="your-email" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-email wpcf7-validates-as-required wpcf7-validates-as-email" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n                        <p class="cformfield">\n                            <label>Subject</label><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap telephone"><input type="tel" name="telephone" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-tel wpcf7-validates-as-required wpcf7-validates-as-tel" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false"></span> </p>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class="col-sm-4">\n                        <p class="cformfieldtext">Your Message\n                            <br><span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap your-message"><textarea name="your-message" cols="40" rows="10" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-textarea" aria-invalid="false" style="overflow: hidden; word-wrap: break-word; height: 96px;"></textarea></span> </p>\n                        <p>\n                            <input type="submit" value="Send" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-submit"><img class="ajax-loader" src="http://realestate.homula.com/wp-content/plugins/contact-form-7/images/ajax-loader.gif" alt="Sending ..." style="visibility: hidden;"></p>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class="clr"></div>\n                    <div class="wpcf7-response-output wpcf7-display-none"></div>\n                </form>\n            </div>\n            <p>Deciding to sell your home is a big step and not something that you want to leave up to chance. Although you might think that listing your home is the first step in the process of selling it, there&rsquo;s actually a lot to do before you make the leap. At Homula, we are experts at connecting you with reputable Toronto real estate agents who will walk you through the entire listing process. Take a look at the things you should consider before listing your home.</p>\n            <h3>Get Estimates for Your Planned Renovations and Upgrades</h3>\n            <p>When you&rsquo;re getting ready to list your home, chances are you&rsquo;re going to be replacing a lot of things that have outlived their welcome &ndash; this could be anything from a new furnace, roof or water heater. However, many people aren&rsquo;t prepared for the financial commitment that comes with this process, so make sure to get some accurate estimates on the costs of your renovations, replacements and upgrades to give you a better idea of how much money you&rsquo;re going to need to shell out.</p>\n            <div class="list_my_house_box_1">\n                <div><strong class="active_strong">Clean</strong><strong>Invest in Curb Appeal</strong><strong>Prepare for Privacy Invasion</strong><strong>Get Your Papers Together</strong></div>\n                <p class="box_1_p_1">No matter how much you hate the idea, you&rsquo;re going to have to accept the fact that listing your home means you&rsquo;re going to have to clean it. And be sure not to skimp &ndash; a light clean isn&rsquo;t going to cut it. Now is the time to invest in some heavy-duty cleanup and get the dirt and grime out of those hard-to-reach areas that you typically pass up on maintaining, such as behind your stove or fridge.</p>\n                <p class="box_1_p_2">Curb appeal refers to how your home looks from the outside and is a crucial part in getting prospective buyers to consider your property. Anything from maintaining your lawn to straightening your mailbox can increase your home&rsquo;s curb appeal. Failing to keep track of such small details might not seem like a big deal, but it can be the difference between people driving by your home and inquiring about purchasing it and disregarding it because of something on the exterior that turned them off.</p>\n                <p class="box_1_p_3">Unless you choose to exclusively do private showings &ndash; something you&rsquo;re <a href="http://realestate.homula.com/find-a-realtor/" target="_blank">realtor</a> will advocate against &ndash; you&rsquo;re going to need to get used to having people in your home on a regular basis. This means strangers in your home opening your closets and cupboards and seeing how you live. Make sure that you are comfortable with this idea before listing your home, and only list it when you are completely sure that your home is in the state that you want it to be presented to prospective buyers.</p>\n                <p class="box_1_p_4">Before you jump into any hands-on work and start renovating, the first step is getting all of your papers together. Anything that you can use to entice the buyer is useful, including applicable warranties, old utility bills, information about the paint colors used on your walls and the operating manuals for your appliances. Providing this information will give the listing agent the impression that you understand the listing process and have everything under control.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div class="list_my_house_box_2">\n                <div><strong class="active_strong">Make Changes</strong><strong>Depersonalize the house</strong><strong>Pricing</strong><strong>Hire a professional Marketer</strong><strong>Know when to sell</strong></div>\n                <p class="box_2_p_1">Real estate prices change depending on the location. In saying that, you should set yourself apart from the neighbours and be the MLS listing that stands out. You can make a great first impression by redoing the front lawn or the roof. Do a bit of research in order to find out what new homeowners are looking for in your area. Then, make the necessary upgrades that will bring you the best return on your investment. Before listing your home, make upgrades to your windows, doors and heating and cooling systems. Having an energy efficient home spikes your property value.</p>\n                <p class="box_2_p_2">People try on new shoes before buying them and they take cars on test drives before making a decision. They do this to get a sense of ownership, and the same rules apply when buying a home. The buyer has to walk in and envision themselves living in that space. If it is cluttered with your personal belongings, they cannot get that feeling. Empty out your home before listing it so that the new owners will be amazed. As an added bonus, the living space looks bigger. Our home evaluators will ensure your home will exceed the needs of potential buyers.</p>\n                <p class="box_2_p_3">At Homula, we understand that many home sellers opt not to use a real estate agent since it will cost extra money. However, a <a href="http://realestate.homula.com/agents/" target="_blank">good agent</a> can save you money in the long run. If you price your home too low, you lose money. If you price it too high, you will not get any offers. If it is left on the market for too long, people will lose interest; they will feel like something is wrong with it. There are many benefits to hiring an agent.</p>\n                <p class="box_2_p_4">Hire a professional to handle all of your marketing needs. They will know how to structure the campaign and they will get professional photographers and cameramen for the pictures and virtual tours. Presentation is everything, and if a potential buyer is not impressed with the preview, the chances are he or she will not come to have a firsthand look.</p>\n                <p class="box_2_p_5">People buy houses all year around. Most houses are bought and sold between March and April. Spring sees the highest activity is the industry since people want to have a comfortable move during the late spring and early summer months. Sure, you have people that buy all year around, but if you want to get it over with quickly, the best time to list your home is at the end of February. If you do have to make outdoor upgrades to the property you might want to aim for an early summer list time.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class="after_box_p">Selling your home can always be a difficult proposition, but if you follow a few simple rules, the process does not last long after listing. Take the above tips into consideration and we guarantee you that you will be as prepared to list your home as you possibly can be.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n', '', '', 2, 0),
(15, 'receive free home report', 'receive-free-home-report', '', '	<div class="container">\n	<div class="row">\n		<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1">\n		<div class="after_title">PLEASE SUBMIT YOUR REQUEST AND TEAM HOMULA WILL FOLLOW UP FOR YOU</div>\n		<form action="/receive-free-home-report" method="post" class="wpcf7-form ng-pristine ng-valid">\n			<div style="display: none;">\n				<input type="hidden" name="_wpcf7" value="1707">\n				<input type="hidden" name="_wpcf7_version" value="4.5.1">\n				<input type="hidden" name="_wpcf7_locale" value="en_US">\n				<input type="hidden" name="_wpcf7_unit_tag" value="wpcf7-f1707-p539-o1">\n				<input type="hidden" name="_wpnonce" value="5120b2b1d6">\n			</div>\n			<p class="cformfield">Your Name (required) <span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap your-name"><input type="text" name="your-name" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span></p>\n			<p class="cformfield">Your Email (required) <span class="wpcf7-form-control-wrap your-email"><input type="email" name="your-email" value="" size="40" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-email wpcf7-validates-as-required wpcf7-validates-as-email" aria-required="true" aria-invalid="false" required></span> </p>\n			<p class="cformbtn"><input type="submit" value="subscribe" class="wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-submit"><img class="ajax-loader" src="http://realestate.homula.com/wp-content/plugins/contact-form-7/images/ajax-loader.gif" alt="Sending ..." style="visibility: hidden;"></p>\n			<div class="wpcf7-response-output wpcf7-display-none"></div>\n		</form>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="current_box_wr">\n		<div class="container">\n	<div class="row">\n	<div class="col-sm-12">\n	<div class="current_box_wr_content">\n	<p>At Homula, we provide our clients with free home reports. A home report is a crucial document that is needed in the Toronto real estate <span style="font-weight: 400;">industry.</span></p>\n\n	<div class="row">\n		<div class="col-sm-6">\n			<div class="current_box">\n				<h3>What is a Home Report?</h3>\n				<p>A home report is a report card that highlights features essential to buyers and sellers of a house. There are firms which provide free home reports and there are instances where you need to pay to have one done. At Homula, we provide you with a home report that is free of cost. Anyone buying or selling a <strong><a class="content-interlink" href="http://realestate.homula.com/" target="_blank">home</a></strong> should have a clear idea as to what such a report pertains to. Almost MLS listing <span style="font-weight: 400;">has received a home report.</span> </p>\n				<p>Many real estate firms have suffered a lawsuit as they were not providing proper home reports. Sales of homes were not being finalized because the reports were missing critical information about the property.</p>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n\n		<div class="col-sm-6">\n			<div class="current_box">\n				<h3>What is Included in a Home Report?</h3>\n				<p>A home report must include a single survey by a certified survey provider on the condition and value of a house. This comes with an in-depth energy report. The energy report includes an energy efficiency rating and an energy performance certificate. This entails a clear outline of gas and electricity bills and potential areas of the home where updates or alterations have to be made to increase energy efficiency. Lastly, the report contains a property questionnaire which includes a list of all the changes made to the property and factoring costs.</p>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n\n		<div class="col-sm-6">\n			<div class="current_box">\n				<h3>How Long is a Home Report?</h3>\n				<p>There is no specific time period that such a report is valid for, but if the property has been on the market for an extended period of time, the buyer has the right to ask for a new report to be constructed. If a prospective buyer does ask for a report, you or your agent must provide them a copy of the report within 10 days.</p>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n\n		<div class="col-sm-6">\n			<div class="current_box">\n				<h3>Can You Refuse a Proposal for a Home Report?</h3>\n				<p>You can refuse the proposal, but you must provide adequate information as to why you are making the refusal. You can refuse it based on the grounds that you believe the buyer does not have the financial means to purchase the home or if you feel the buyer is not a serious player and you have other options available to you. Under no circumstance is a seller allowed to refuse a home report based on discriminatory factors. There are instances however, that if you are marketing your own home, you can generate your own home report. In such an instance, the report has a validity period and the buyer can chose to refuse your estimates. The buyer is allowed to make the demand that the report be prepared by a certified professional.</p>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n\n		<div class="col-sm-6">\n			<div class="current_box">\n				<h3>Is a Home Report Always Required?</h3>\n				<p>There are also instances where a report is not required. New housing or newly converted premises does not require a home report. This is because the property has to be built or remodelled according to building codes and regulations. For example, a new house cannot have out of date ventilation piping or heating and cooling equipment that does not meet energy standards. A home report is one of the most trustworthy pieces of documentation during a real estate transaction. There are severe penalties if it comes to light that any information on a report was falsified, during the marketing process. A transaction cannot be completed without a proper, methodical and calculative home report, and <a class="content-interlink" href="http://realestate.homula.com/agents/" target="_blank">our experts </a>know can assist you with this today.</p>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	</div>\n	</div>\n	</div>\n	</div>\n</div>\n', '', '', 2, 0);
