	                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> 905-822-0010</li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li></li>\r\n	            </ul>\r\n	        </div>\r\n	    </div>\r\n	    <div class="agent-row-content ">\r\n	        <h2 class="agent-row-title"><strong>Baker Street Home Inspections</strong></h2>\r\n	        <hr>\r\n	        <div class="agent-row-info">\r\n	            Ed Nakon\r\n	            <ul>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> 416-483-3535</li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i> <a> info@bakerstreet-hi.ca</a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i> <a>www.bakerstreet-hi.ca</a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li></li>\r\n	            </ul>\r\n	        </div>\r\n	    </div>\r\n	    <div class="agent-row-content ">\r\n	        <h2 class="agent-row-title"><strong>Avanti Home Inspection </strong></h2>\r\n	        <hr>\r\n	        <div class="agent-row-info">\r\n	            Russ Fasvlo\r\n	            <ul>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> 416-605-3651</li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i> <a>www.ahminspections.ca</a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li></li>\r\n	            </ul>\r\n	        </div>\r\n	    </div>\r\n	    <div class="agent-row-content ">\r\n	        <h2 class="agent-row-title"><strong>Ander Home Inspection Max Ander</strong></h2>\r\n	        <hr>\r\n	        <div class="agent-row-info">\r\n	            Max Ander\r\n	            <ul>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> 416-223-4100</li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li></li>\r\n	            </ul>\r\n	        </div>\r\n	    </div>\r\n	    <div class="agent-row-content ">\r\n	        <h2 class="agent-row-title"><strong>AmeriSpec Inspection Services</strong></h2>\r\n	        <hr>\r\n	        <div class="agent-row-info">\r\n	            Maria\r\n	            <ul>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> 416-465-8689</li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li></li>\r\n	            </ul>\r\n	        </div>\r\n	    </div>\r\n	    <div class="agent-row-content ">\r\n	        <h2 class="agent-row-title"><strong>AmeriSpec Inspection Services</strong></h2>\r\n	        <hr>\r\n	        <div class="agent-row-info">\r\n	            John Manis\r\n	            <ul>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> 905-780-9068</li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li></li>\r\n	            </ul>\r\n	        </div>\r\n	    </div>\r\n	    <div class="agent-row-content ">\r\n	        <h2 class="agent-row-title"><strong>Allen &amp; Bennett                                                        </strong></h2>\r\n	        <hr>\r\n	        <div class="agent-row-info">\r\n	            Allen &amp; Bennett Andrew Bennett\r\n	            <ul>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> 416-751-0682</li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i>\r\n	                    <a> </a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i> <a>www.amerispec.com</a>\r\n	                </li>\r\n	                <li></li>\r\n	            </ul>\r\n	        </div>\r\n	    </div>\r\n	    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Our expert </span>Toronto real estate <span style="font-weight: 400;">agents at Homula provide home inspections for the purpose of providing you with vital information about your property. Receiving a home inspection will be of great benefit to you. You should have your home inspected before it is labeled as an </span>MLS Listing.<span style="font-weight: 400;"> There are a few things to remember before going forward with an evaluation and we have listed them below. </span>\r\n	    </p>\r\n	    <p><b>Upgrades</b>\r\n	    </p>\r\n	    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Make updates to your home before the evaluation. First and foremost, do a little something that will differentiate your home from all the other houses on the street. Put in a flower bed on your front lawn, or something simple yet elegant that catches the eye. First impressions are everything, and a little feature that sets you apart is essential. </span>\r\n	    </p>\r\n	    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Secondly, repair leaky faucets or broken windows. Keep in mind that evaluators appraise homes in 500 dollar increments. Something as inconspicuous as a missing hand rail can have a huge impact on the final financial value of your house. A <a href="http://realestate.homula.com/property-management/">property manager</a> can assist you with this.</span>\r\n	    </p>\r\n	    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Third thing to remember is, be careful what you spend your money on. There is a common misconception that nicer kitchens and bathrooms really increase the value of your home. That is not entirely true. </span>\r\n	    </p>\r\n	    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n	    <h3>Research</h3>\r\n	    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n	    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/agents/"><strong>Our agents</strong></a> will do some research in order to see what home buyers in your area are looking for. A working couple with a stringent schedule may not be looking into a fancy, fully stocked, restaurant level kitchen. Bathroom and kitchen remodels are expensive; if it looks fine keep it that way. Keep some money aside for a paint job or new doors. These are little changes that can create a major impact on the final evaluation for your home. </span>\r\n	    </p>\r\n	    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n	    <h3>Actual Age Vs. Effective Age</h3>\r\n	    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n	    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The last thing is the difference between actual age and effective age. If you have a century old home, look at changes you can make to improve effective age. Do not waste time and money on upgrades that do not improve the effective age of your home. You may need to hire a builder to give you tips on what to do, but it is something that is required. If you have a century old home with an effective age between 3 to 5 years, you have a very appealing piece of property. After you make all the updates that are needed, give a list of all the changes to the evaluator. The appraiser can use the list when your home is put up for sale. </span>\r\n	    </p>\r\n	    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n	    <h3>Personal Touch</h3>\r\n	    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n	    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Before having an evaluation, provide details about everything you like about your house. Mention little details about your house that really appeals to you. This might be something the evaluator can relate to and the same can be said about a potential buyer. Also, talk about the neighbourhood in general – all the features about your neighbours and locality you like. If there is a nice place five minutes away that serves spectacular chicken wings, mention it. </span>\r\n	    </p>\r\n	    <h3>Clean Up</h3>\r\n	    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n	    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You might be thinking to yourself, dirty dishes in the sink or a half finished motorbike in the garage will not affect the property value. A home evaluation paints a complete picture. The property may be in perfect condition, but when an appraiser sees a messy area, it could affect your property’s value. </span>\r\n	    </p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', '', '', 5, 0);
