(26, 'leasing agent', 'leasing-agent', '', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">At Homula, we connect you with top notch leasing agents. The process of leasing comes along with many procedures and real estate laws. Any Toronto real estate professional would agree that it is imperative for you to have an understanding of what leasing really is.</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>Everything you need to know about Commercial and Residential leasing</h3>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">A commercial lease is very different from a residential lease. It is an agreement between a tenant and landlord for the use of a particular property for business practices. It is a point of operation for a business entity. Signing a lease is a two part process. First, you sign an offer lease, and if you reach an agreement, you sign a lease which contains the finalized offer, highlighting the details of the negotiations.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Whenever you are looking to lease, always look to negotiate. You do not have to agree to the landlord’s stipulations immediately. With leasing, there is always a little wiggle room. Our professionals will be ready before you finalize any paperwork. Our<a href="http://realestate.homula.com/real-estate-lawyer/"><strong> real estate lawyers</strong></a> can take a look at the lease and have a realtor look at the property. Make sure you are not being taken for a spin. Similarly, any changes to negotiations have to written. Verbal negotiations do not hold up in court without paperwork backing it up. If anything seems fishy, be ready to walk away. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">With commercial real estate there are different types of leases. The lease may be for a fixed term or it may be renewable after a certain time. The rent for commercial properties is always based on the space itself; it is priced according to square footage. This information may not be included in the </span>. <span style="font-weight: 400;">There are 3 different types of leases:</span>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Percentage rent lease: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is mostly for retail places. You pay a base rent and then you pay a certain percentage of your sales. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Gross rental lease:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> You pay a flat rate which equals to the base rent and you pay other expenses you have negotiated with your landlord. The Landlord covers some of the operating cost. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Net lease:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> There are three different kinds of net leases. Single net is when you pay some of the taxes plus base rent. Double net is when you pay insurance costs to the landlord in addition to some of the taxes and base rent. Triple net is when you cover any and all expenses associated with the property. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Our home inspectors come in and measure the property, so that you can be certain that you are paying for the space which is being advertised. By hiring a real estate lawyer to read the lease, you can be clear as to exactly what you are paying for. An expert will be able to tell you exactly what the lease covers. Things such as, parking, utilities, cleaning services and security are extremely important to many people. A <a href="http://realestate.homula.com/home-inspector/"><strong>home inspection</strong></a> will allow you to see if there are any repairs that need to be made. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Many people want to have a commercial lease that enables them to make changes during the term. Your business may expand and you may outgrow your given space. Some people want options in their lease that allows them to sublet to a third party without their landlord’s permission. In addition, many people want a lease that lets you make changes to your property to increase productivity or for marketing purposes. Make all of your requirements very clear to your real estate lawyer.</span>', '', '', 5, 0),
(27, 'real estate lawyer', 'real-estate-lawyer', '', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">As a current or aspiring home owner, it’s imperative for you to understand the key terms that are used by </span>Toronto real estate <span style="font-weight: 400;">experts on a daily basis. Having a good understanding of the entire real estate industry will be of great benefit to you. Below, we’ll translate terms that are extremely important and relevant to real estate law. </span>\r\n<h3>What is Real Estate/Real Property Law?</h3>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The legal definition of real property or real estate is land and the buildings that are on it. Real estate can either be <a href="http://homula.idxbroker.com/idx/search/commercial-search">commercial</a> or residential. Every single </span>MLS listing <span style="font-weight: 400;">falls under the category “real estate.” </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Real estate can either be owned by one or many people. It can be purchased by one person, and rented out or leased by another through rental agreements. Due to the fact that there are many different requirements and agreements involved in the entire processes of buying, selling, leasing, renting and investing, the need for a real estate lawyer is crucial. For the simple fact that land can be sold our bought at an extremely high price, there have been a plethora of laws put in place in order to ensure the real estate transactions are recorded correctly. Governments have set certain laws in order to determine which land is available for use and what can be done to that land. </span>\r\n<h3>Key Real Estate Terms</h3>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Escrow:</strong> Property of money that is securely held by a disinterested, third party. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Foreclosure:</strong> If the owner fails to pay back the mortgage, it is during this process that the lender will take back the house. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Title:</strong> A legal term that is used to describe who owns the land. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Closing:</strong> The meeting that occurs when ownership has been officially transferred. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Mortgage:</strong> This is a loan that covers the entire cost of the house.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Insurance Law:</strong> Homeowner insurance protects your property from damages.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Landlord Tenant Law:</strong> This law covers the rules around renting real estate, which includes, leasing and eviction for commercial and residential tenants. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Estate Planning:</strong> When people would like to keep real estate within their family, estate planning attorneys assist them with the process of doing so. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Tax Law:</strong> Having real estate that is mortgaged, or real estate in general, has a huge effect on the household’s taxes. Every homeowner is required to pay property taxes and should understand the tax code so that they don’t over or under pay. </span>\r\n<h3>Benefit of Having a Real Estate Lawyer</h3>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Without legal assistance, real estate transactions can be extremely difficult to understand. The investment in which you need to make in order to receive expert legal assistance is well worth it. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Expert real estate lawyers oversee the legalities that are involved in both selling and buying property in order to ensure their client is granted with fair and equal rights. These lawyers check the title of ownership to the property for any liabilities or issues, such as, liens.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">All in all, real estate lawyers protect buyers and sells from financial loss. </span><a class="content-interlink" href="http://realestate.homula.com/contact-us/"><b>Contact us</b></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> today in order to connect with an expert real estate lawyer!</span>', '', '', 5, 0),
