s="fa fa-phone"></i> </li>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i> <a> info@lastdetail.ca</a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i>\r\n                    <a> </a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="agent-row-content ">\r\n        <h2 class="agent-row-title"><strong>Aztec Incorporated                                                        </strong></h2>\r\n        <hr>\r\n        <div class="agent-row-info">\r\n            Kevin Jones\r\n            <ul>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> </li>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i> <a> aztec@rogers.com </a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i>\r\n                    <a> </a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="agent-row-content ">\r\n        <h2 class="agent-row-title"><strong>A Gross Improvement                                                        </strong></h2>\r\n        <hr>\r\n        <div class="agent-row-info">\r\n\r\n            Andrea Gross\r\n            <ul>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> 905-580-1293</li>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i> <a> agrossimprovement@gmail.com </a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i> <a>www.agrossimprovement.com </a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n	<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">At Homula, we have expert home stagers with the ability to ensure your commercial or residential property is ready to dominate the </span><b>Toronto real estate </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">market. </span><b><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/about-us/">Our experts </a>&nbsp;</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">will make sure your space is inviting at the first glance! Homes that are free of clutter, decorated and nicely laid out sell 10x faster than homes that are left as is. Our home stagers will allow your </span><b>MLS listing </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">to stand out. Our duties include, but are not limited to: </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Asses your needs </span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Furnish your home </span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Decorate </span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Continuously visit the property until it is sold </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In addition to our home staging services, we have provided with ways in which you can increase your property value:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You might be wondering what types of improvements you can easily make to increase the value of your home. What will urge the house seekers to buy your home out of all that is available on the market? There are a number of small things that you can do to make a huge difference in the value or perceived value of your home. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hire a Pro</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You will want to take any advice your </span><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/agents/"><b>realtor </b></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">can provide you with to heart. This goes back to hiring one of expert home stagers to help you understand how you can improve the interior space of your home. They might be able to offer tips and tricks that are easy to do and that will increase the value of your home. Sometimes it can be as simple as moving furniture around, painting, removing items from the walls and more. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Inspect Your Home</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You should </span><b><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/home-inspector/">hire an inspector</a></b><span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;to look at your home before you put it up on the market. An inspector may be able to find hidden problems with your home that could be impacting its value. An inspector might be able to see things that you wouldn’t otherwise notice or consider. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Paint </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the simplest and most cost effective improvement tips is to paint. A freshly painted room just looks nice and presentable. It can make your space seem more open and welcoming to buyers. Try to choose colours that are more neutral and not too out there. Simple is best when it comes to paint. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Maximize energy efficiency </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You will want to get a professional to assess the energy efficiency of your home. You can then decide if there are small fixes you can do to help increase the energy efficiency of your home. People nowadays are very conscious about energy conservation. It can be a very important factor when they are considering purchasing a home. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Landscaping</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The way your home looks from the outside is very important. A buyer will be distracted by long grass or a poorly maintained property. You should do some low maintenance landscaping and make sure the gardens look nice. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cleanliness counts </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ensure your home is tidy and well organized. This goes a long way when people consider your home. They want to feel immediately comfortable in the space and it can be distracting if there is too much clutter.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Visually increase space </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The size of your home will affect the value of it. You can do some things to make the rooms in your house feel larger than they actually are. Maybe you are able to open up a wall to make a more open concept feel. Maybe you can just add a large mirror to the room to give the illusion of more space. You can also open up the blinds or curtains to let the light shine in as this will help to make the rooms feel larger. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">These are just a few things you can do to increase the value of your home. Your</span><b><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/agents/"> real estate agent</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">will be able to offer many more tips and tricks for you to try. </span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>	', '', '', 5, 0),
(29, 'graphic designer', 'graphic-designer', '', '<p><strong>Graphic Designer</strong> Your success as a real estate agent depends on many factors, from the way you navigate the MLS listing service to better serve your clients to the way you network for referrals. The single most important factor, however, is how you choose to present yourself through your printed material. This is why finding a graphic designer you can work with is essential. Your knowledge of the Toronto real estate market is what will help you become a hit with your clients, but the way they choose your services to begin with depends on the strength of your materials. <strong> How Can A Graphic Designer Help?</strong> A graphic designer can do a surprising number of things for you and your marketability. He or she can help you market yourself in a way you simply can&rsquo;t on your own. They can do so by creating materials that: &bull; Inform your clients about you &bull; Indicate what services you provide &bull; Develop your brand in a unique but professional way Developing your brand is a multifaceted task that shouldn&rsquo;t be taken lightly. Your graphic designer will help create postcards, brochures, your logo, business cards, banner ads, and other images. These are the tools you will use to advertise yourself as an expert in the real estate industry so they need to be professional and sleek. You want to attract the highest quality of customer, and a graphic designer can help make that happen. <strong> Where To Start</strong> The best place to start is to look at the promotional materials that your colleagues are distributing. From there you can get an idea of what words, what doesn&rsquo;t, and what type of materials you find to be best in line with the image you want to project. After you&rsquo;ve settled on a stylistic approach you prefer, make a list of all the materials you want your designer to take care of for you. Be sure to discuss your budget and your intentions with your graphic designer ahead of time, to ensure a smooth relationship. <strong>Figure Out Where Your Priorities Lie</strong> If you&rsquo;re unhappy with your website, or don&rsquo;t have one at all, it&rsquo;s a good idea to start here. Your prospective clients are turning to online browsing in growing numbers, and will want to see a sleek and professional website before they decide to hire you. Move on to advertising materials after that, and decide how you want to approach marketing yourself. Ask your designer about setting up social media accounts, and be sure to specify that you need images for those pages. <strong>How To Choose A Graphic Designer</strong> Homula has a comprehensive list of graphic designers, each one with experience and expertise in the real estate industry. Start your search with Homula, taking the time to visit each designer&rsquo;s website and take a look at their portfolios. Certain graphic designers will have specific stylistic approaches to the work they complete, so be sure you pick one with a style you like. Pick a designer who has talent and creativity, to ensure that your materials don&rsquo;t look like everyone else&rsquo;s. Remember that you want to stand out in the field, and that quality doesn&rsquo;t come at the lowest available price. <strong>Contact Homula For More</strong> To learn more about how a graphic designer can help you get your real estate business off the ground and to expand your customer base, contact Homula. We have a full list of graphic designers available, who can help you achieve your sales goals.</p>\r\n', '', '', 5, 0),
