>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i>\r\n                    <a> </a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i>\r\n                    <a> </a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li>COLLINGWOOD</li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="agent-row-content ">\r\n        <h2 class="agent-row-title"><strong>Ali &amp; Kim LLP</strong></h2>\r\n        <hr>\r\n        <div class="agent-row-info">\r\n            Ayoub Ali\r\n            <ul>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-phone"></i> 905-826-3421</li>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-at"></i> <a> info@streetsvillelaw.com</a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><i class="fa fa-globe"></i> <a>www.streetsvillelaw.com </a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li>WEST</li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p><strong>Lawyers (FIRMS)</strong>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>Once you’ve found your dream home or placed your own on the Toronto real estate market, the next step is to find a law firm who can represent you in this transaction. Many people have a negative opinion of lawyers, and may even caution you against hiring one for real estate transactions. While it isn’t a legal requirement to have a law firm represent a seller or a buyer, it can go along way to protecting you if anything happens to go wrong, and ensures that your rights are respected. Once you’ve navigated the MLS listing, found your home, or are ready to sell your old one, you should consult with a lawyer to assist you with the rest of the process.</p>\r\n    <p><strong>Experience In The Field</strong>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>Real estate lawyers have tons of experience in the industry. From taking highly specialized courses while still in law school, to acquiring on the job training, real estate lawyers are able to anticipate problems before they arise, and can help advise you against making uninformed decisions. Together with your real estae agent, they can review your Agreement of Purchase and Sale, and advise you on your rights and obligations under that agreement. They can also work with mortgage professionals to help you get funding for your new home, and will hold funds in escrow until the transaction is completed.</p>\r\n    <p><strong>Certify Title And Assist With Boundary Issues</strong>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>Certifying title isn’t overly important when it comes to purchasing a brand new home, but if you are working with another homeowner to purchase an older home, it’s essential that you ensure title is certified. Simply put, this means that there are no other individuals who could have a claim on your home, and that the current owners are in a position to sell. Lawyers are the only professionals who are authorized to complete this very essential service, which will help protect you against any unpleasant title surprises in the future. Lawyers can also advise you about any potential boundary issues, which comes in handy in cases where fences or shrubbery are installed in the wrong location. Even minor boundary disputes can turn into costly legal battles in the future, when you or your neighbour want to sell.\r\n        <br>\r\n        <strong><br>\r\nProtect Your Rights</strong>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>Lawyers will ensure that your rights are protected throughout the entire process. This firm will ensure that you don’t enter into any agreements that will prove to be detrimental or costly to you in the future, and helps guard against being taken advantage of by a seller. No one likes to think that this will happen, but if it does, it can be more expensive to you in the long run without a lawyer on your side.</p>\r\n    <p><strong>Contact Homula For More</strong>\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>To find a reputable real estate firm who can represent you each step of the way, contact Homula. We have a complete listing of the best legal firms serving the area, all of whom have experienced law