heir contracts. </span><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/agents/">Our experts </a><span style="font-weight: 400;">read between the lines and watch out for any hidden fees. At Homula, we have strong connections with a lot of lenders. Our brokers could even get you a special discount rate from a lender because he/she brings in so much business for that particular lending institution. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The alternative to hiring one of our brokers is spending hours ploughing through dozens of lenders, looking for the right one. Our experts will save you both time and money. There are a lot of fees associated with getting a new mortgage, like application fees and appraisal fees. Our professionals might get a lender to waive some of the fees or get you a contract where the fees are much more favourable. Little things like that make a broker extremely helpful.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Choosing a Broker</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Working with Homula is an excellent idea. Outside of Homula, some brokers are commission salesmen. Their main objective is to get you into a mortgage that gives them the highest compensation. You are looking at a contract with a low interest rate and similarly low fees. You are in it for the long haul, but the broker is thinking about short term profit. As a result, depending on the broker, you might not see eye to eye and you might not get the best deal. Also, mortgage brokers cannot provide estimates. A broker&rsquo;s estimates may not be accurate and the lender may choose to change the terms on the final agreement. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To summarize the pros and the cons, the best thing you can do is </span><a href="http://realestate.homula.com/contact-us/"><b>contact </b></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">a reputable mortgage broker today. </span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', '', 6, 0),
